<table width="100%" cellpadding="4" cellspacing="0" border="0" align="center" class="forumline">
	<tr>
		<th class="thHead" align="left">Upcoming Shadowbane Game Changes</th>
	</tr>

	<tr>
		<td class="row1"><span class="postbody">Prior to the Secrets of Power update (Patch 3.0), we will be releasing a mini-patch that will adjust some of the basic game play mechanics and features of Shadowbane. These changes are being made to make every day of playing Shadowbane more enjoyable, while also helping players reach the best part of the game faster - Siegeing!  
<br />

<br />
All of these changes come from Community requests and feedback. They have also been debated and discussed at length with both our Developer Focus Groups and Class Advocates.
<br />

<br />
Here are a few of the changes we are planning to implement:
<br />

<br />
Experience gained per kill will be permanently increased. 
<br />
The rate at which creatures (non-player characters) dodge attacks will be reduced. 
<br />
The wear and tear (item decay) on equipped items following player death will be reduced. 
<br />
The amount of gold required to refine training points will be reduced. 
<br />
The level cap on Safeholds (on the mainland) will be increased to Level 49. 
<br />
PvP Kill Messages will now be broadcast to the guild of the individual who was victorious (example: Ashen Temper has killed Gimpli of Nurfed) 
<br />
These are a few of the changes requested by the Community team, and they will be thoroughly tested on Test Server soon. If any adjustments are needed to these changes, they will be reconfigured and re-tested before releasing on the Live servers. The Design Team is still examining many other proposals, changes, and ideas to make Shadowbane more accessible to various play types and styles. 
<br />

<br />
Please give us your comments and feedback on these upcoming changes!
<br />

<br />
By: Vosx ...<br /><a href=".//forum/viewtopic.php?t=342&amp;sid=ac555ad718cfc97c38416a7752608b58"><span class="gensmall">Read more</span></a>&nbsp;</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
